<br>
The original intent was for it to be a massive boost to damage for 36seconds then a big bang pbaoe. Well, after a few mages got it and discovered that it was broken, they admitted that it was broken and 'fixxed' it. The fix didn't work.<br>
<br>
The skill should either take our current pet or summon a new 'frenzy pet' that has most/all of the following properties:<br>
1) Immune to aoe's similar to wizzy familiar.<br>
2) Output damage at a rate equivalent to a fully hasted lvl60 monk in decent weaponry.<br>
3) Last the entire duration of the fight ala Rage of Zoom (with no method of adding any new mob to the hate list. 1mob and 1mob only)<br>
4) Be unbuffable/healable. The pet should already come fully hasted with a sufficient atk rating such that no player buffs would benefit the pet. We don't want the pet to be healable or else it would make a FB mage + cleric a viable duo on many mobs they shouldn't be able to duo. In situations where pet would be used, it would take no damage anyways (other than Enrage, which i personally feel should follow the 'pets avoid riposte damage' rule).<br>
5) The whole pbaoe poofing of the pet becomes moot when it's alive for the duration of the battle, so that still broken aspect of FB would be eliminated.<br>
<br>
The 'cost' to activate the skill needs to have 2 requirements. 3 potential requirements are listed, of which only 2 should be in place.<br>
1) Recast. This should be between 1-2 game days so it's usable on multiple 'bosses' when clearing NToV for example.<br>
2) Mana usage. Would a guild really sacrafice a magicians trans rods for an extra monk's dmg? Because that's what we'd become if it used our entire manapool (and trying to code it to have varying power based upon the actual manapool when cast would be a nightmare). Preferably it would cost ~1000mana to cast. This would still be sizable chunk of mana, but wouldn't render us unable to make rods for a couple minutes after use.<br>
3) Reagent. Obviously a more expensive reagent would limit its use just as much as a long recast time.<br>
<br>
That is how I have always envisioned Frenzied Burnout. Certainly not overpowering with it's limitations, but definately a viable offensive damage AA skill. As FB currently exists, i refuse to waste the points on it.<br>
